casebody.data:
JOHNSON v. WILKINS, WARDEN. No. 141,

Misc.

Decided October 14, 1963. Appellant pro se. Louis J. Lefkowitz, Attorney General of New York, Paxton Blair, Solicitor General, and Winifred C. Stanley, Assistant Attorney General, for appellee. Per Curiam.

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed for want of a substantial federal question.
